CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 22, 1945, pg. 8, reads: "Four Generations! - When the charming group shown above came to Pittsburgh to visit Mrs. Robert L. Vann, it brought four generations of Mrs. Vann's Family (the Matthewes of Gettysburg, Pa.) together. Left to right: Mrs. Joseph Wanzel, wife of Mrs. Vann's great-nephew; Mrs. Edna Reed, sister to Mrs. Vann, holding baby Joan Wanzel, great-great-niece, while Mrs. Mary Penn, daughter of Mrs. Reed, stands by.  They were entertained delightfully during their stay in Sycamore Manor, Mrs. Vann's home in Oakmont. - Courier Photo by Harris."
TitMainTitle: Jessie Vann, Mary Penn holding baby Joan Wanzel, Edna Reed, and Mrs. Joseph Wanzel, posed in garden of Vann estate Sycamore Manor, Oakmont
